"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713690","Department of Health","false","2017-04-05","<p>The fraction of annual all-cause adult mortality attributable to anthropogenic (human-made) particulate air pollution (measured as fine particulate matter, PM<sub>2.5</sub>) is provided by the Public Health Outcomes Framework (PHOF) indicator 3.01.</p><p> </p><p>This calculates the mortality burden associated with long-term exposure to anthropogenic particulate air pollution at current levels, expressed as the percentage of annual deaths from all causes in those aged over 30.</p><p> </p><p>The following table shows the fraction of mortality (%) attributable to particulate air pollution extracted from the PHOF 3.01 indicator, for the period 2010-2015, for England, North West and areas within the Greater Manchester Area (GMA), as GMA is not an administrative area.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>2015</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Greater Manchester</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Bolton</p></td><td><p>5.0</p></td><td><p>4.7</p></td><td><p>4.9</p></td><td><p>4.8</p></td><td><p>4.2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Bury</p></td><td><p>5.2</p></td><td><p>4.8</p></td><td><p>4.9</p></td><td><p>4.8</p></td><td><p>4.0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Manchester</p></td><td><p>5.4</p></td><td><p>5.1</p></td><td><p>5.2</p></td><td><p>5.1</p></td><td><p>4.3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Oldham</p></td><td><p>5.3</p></td><td><p>5.0</p></td><td><p>5.0</p></td><td><p>4.9</p></td><td><p>4.2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Rochdale</p></td><td><p>5.2</p></td><td><p>4.8</p></td><td><p>4.8</p></td><td><p>4.7</p></td><td><p>4.0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Salford</p></td><td><p>5.5</p></td><td><p>5.2</p></td><td><p>5.3</p></td><td><p>5.2</p></td><td><p>4.3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Stockport</p></td><td><p>5.2</p></td><td><p>4.8</p></td><td><p>4.9</p></td><td><p>4.7</p></td><td><p>4.1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Tameside</p></td><td><p>5.4</p></td><td><p>5.0</p></td><td><p>5.0</p></td><td><p>4.8</p></td><td><p>4.2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Trafford</p></td><td><p>5.1</p></td><td><p>4.8</p></td><td><p>4.9</p></td><td><p>4.8</p></td><td><p>4.1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Wigan</p></td><td><p>4.8</p></td><td><p>4.6</p></td><td><p>4.9</p></td><td><p>4.7</p></td><td><p>4.3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>North West</p></td><td><p>4.6</p></td><td><p>4.4</p></td><td><p>4.6</p></td><td><p>4.4</p></td><td><p>4.1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>England</p></td><td><p>5.4</p></td><td><p>5.1</p></td><td><p>5.3</p></td><td><p>5.1</p></td><td><p>4.7</p></td></tr></tbody></table>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy",,"2017-04-05T14:14:42.773Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713690/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713690/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713690/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-23","Air Pollution: Greater Manchester","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many deaths have been attributed to air pollution in Greater Manchester in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Baroness Featherstone",,"Baroness Featherstone","HL6287"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713691","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-03-29","<p>The Autumn Statement stated that the green paper will be published in the spring and we are working to that timescale.</p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton",,"2017-03-29T14:45:47.797Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713691/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713691/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713691/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-03-23","Consumers: Protection","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government when they plan to publish the green paper on consumers and markets, as announced in the Budget.","false","Biography information for Baroness Hayter of Kentish Town",,"Baroness Hayter of Kentish Town","HL6288"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713692","Department for International Trade","false","2017-04-06","<p>Until the UK leaves the EU, we will remain subject to EU trade and investment agreements and policy. We will in due course consider all options in the design of future bilateral trade and investment agreements.</p>",,"Lord Price",,"2017-04-06T13:01:06.093Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713692/answer","Biography information for Lord Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713692/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713692/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-03-23","Foreign Investment in UK","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, in the light of the UK's exit from the EU, whether they are planning to introduce primary legislation dealing with foreign investment in UK companies.","false","Biography information for Baroness Hayter of Kentish Town",,"Baroness Hayter of Kentish Town","HL6289"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713693","Department of Health","false","2017-03-28","<p>The Government is committed to the safe and effective regulation of medical devices in the United Kingdom. We continue to strengthen safety while ensuring patients and the public have fast access to new, innovative devices.</p><p> </p><p>We will be implementing the new Devices Regulations, the first provisions of which are expected to enter into force in May this year. Details of the future legislative framework will be subject to the outcome of negotiations with the European Union.</p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy",,"2017-03-28T13:24:25.037Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713693/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713693/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713693/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-23","Medical Equipment: EU Law","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what plans they have to transpose the forthcoming EU Medical Devices Regulation into UK law following the UK's exit from the EU; and how they intend to address those aspects of the Regulation that are based on participation in EU institutions and the single market.","false","Biography information for Baroness Hayter of Kentish Town",,"Baroness Hayter of Kentish Town","HL6290"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713694","Cabinet Office","false","2017-04-06","<p>There has been no change to the appointments process, which is that appointments to the House of Lords continue to be made by the Sovereign on the recommendation of the Prime Minister. This includes those nominations for non party political peerages made on the advice of the House of Lords Appointments Commission. There have been no changes made to the Commission's remit. Any future announcements about appointments to the House of Lords will be made in the usual way.</p>",,"Lord Young of Cookham",,"2017-04-06T14:28:59.63Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713694/answer","Biography information for Lord Young of Cookham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713694/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713694/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-03-23","Peers: Public Appointments","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether there is a moratorium on the appointment of new peers by the House of Lords Appointment Commission; whether the Commission has recommended any new peers since the last set of appointments in October 2015; and whether it plans to appoint any new peers in 2017.","false","Biography information for Baroness Jones of Moulsecoomb",,"Baroness Jones of Moulsecoomb","HL6291"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713695","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-04-03","<p>The Government remains focused on re-establishing an inclusive, devolved government that the overwhelming majority of the people in Northern Ireland want to see. Progress has been made in recent discussions which provide a basis for further intensive discussions to resolve outstanding issues. If these further talks are successful, it would be the Government’s intention quickly to bring forward legislation after the Easter recess to allow an Executive to be formed and avoid a second Assembly election. The Secretary of State for Northern Ireland will be keeping the situation under close review.</p>",,"Lord Dunlop",,"2017-04-03T14:03:34.81Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713695/answer","Biography information for Lord Dunlop","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713695/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713695/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-03-23","Northern Ireland Government","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they have any plans to bring forward legislation to prevent a second Northern Ireland Assembly election this year if there is no agreement to form a new Executive.","false","Biography information for Baroness Jones of Moulsecoomb",,"Baroness Jones of Moulsecoomb","HL6292"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713696","Attorney General","false","2017-04-03","<p>The Crown Prosecution Service’s publicly available legal guidance concerning corporate manslaughter accurately reflects the CPS’s policy on prosecuting for this offence. The guidance includes a requirement for cases to which the guidance may ultimately apply to be referred to the Special Crime Unit of the Special Crime and Counter Terrorism Division.</p>",,"Lord Keen of Elie",,"2017-04-03T13:08:46.397Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713696/answer","Biography information for Lord Keen of Elie","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713696/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713696/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2017-03-23","Corporate Manslaughter: Prosecutions","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord Keen of Elie on 9 March (HL5640), whether the legal guidance for prosecutors concerning the Corporate Manslaughter and Corporate Homicide Act 2007, as set out on the Crown Prosecution Service’s website at 14 March, is current; and whether the Special Crime Unit in the Special Crime and Counter Terrorism Division, CPS Headquarters, continues to maintain an overview of corporate manslaughter cases, as set out in the penultimate paragraph of that advice.","false","Biography information for Lord Knight of Weymouth",,"Lord Knight of Weymouth","HL6293"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713697","Cabinet Office","false","2017-04-03","<p>The independent Advisory Committee on Business Appointments provides its advice direct to the former Minister in question.</p><p>The Committee’s final advice is published online when an appointment has been taken up and/or publicly announced. Until this point, the process is confidential between the Committee and the former Minister in question, to allow for free and frank discussion.</p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Lord Young of Cookham",,"2017-04-03T16:15:09.333Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713697/answer","Biography information for Lord Young of Cookham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713697/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713697/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-03-23","Former Ministers","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether the Advisory Committee on Business Appointments has ever advised a former minister not to accept an appointment.","false","Biography information for Lord Myners",,"Lord Myners","HL6294"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713698","Department for International Trade","false","2017-04-06","<p>According to the latest data from the FCO Economics Unit (2015), UK exports (goods and services) to Bosnia and Herzegovina were £57 million with UK imports reaching £53 million in 2015. (Data for 2016 will be published in April). In FY 2017/18 the HMG team based in Sarajevo will continue to promote trade opportunities across the mining, oil and gas, retail, infrastructure and security sectors which will include a series of tailored events in Bosnia and Herzegovina, the UK and across the wider Central and Eastern European region.</p>",,"Lord Price",,"2017-04-06T14:42:28.24Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713698/answer","Biography information for Lord Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713698/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713698/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-03-23","Trade Promotion: Bosnia and Herzegovina","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what steps they are taking to promote trade between the UK and Bosnia and Herzegovina.","false","Biography information for The Earl of Dundee",,"The Earl of Dundee","HL6295"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713699","Department for International Trade","false","2017-04-06","<p>There are a number of economic opportunities in Bosnia and Herzegovina for UK investors, with software development, mining and oil exploration identified as particular sectors of opportunity. However, HMG also recognises that for more investment to succeed Bosnia and Herzegovina needs to make significant improvements to its business environment, including tackling excess regulation and increasing transparency around public procurement and licensing. The UK is funding projects to improve the business environment by simplifying the process of setting up a business and moving to a 'one-stop' shop system.</p>",,"Lord Price",,"2017-04-06T14:33:03.797Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713699/answer","Biography information for Lord Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713699/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713699/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-03-23","Overseas Investment: Bosnia and Herzegovina","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of economic opportunities for British business for investment and partnership in Bosnia and Herzegovina.","false","Biography information for The Earl of Dundee",,"The Earl of Dundee","HL6296"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713700","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-06","<p>The Government remains committed to driving reform, embedding stability and addressing shared challenges, such as security and migration, in Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH). At the 20 September 2016 General Affairs Council, the EU agreed that the Commission should issue a questionnaire to BiH authorities to assess the country's readiness to be granted candidate country status. That process is continuing. We will continue to support the reforms required through our bilateral engagement (including approximately £6.63 million in programme assistance in financial year 2016-17), in order to ensure BiH becomes a more stable, secure and prosperous country.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns","HL6298","2017-04-06T14:36:21.033Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713700/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713700/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713700/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-23","Bosnia and Herzegovina: EU Enlargement","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what advice they are giving to give Bosnia and Herzegovina to prepare for its acceptance as a candidate country to join the EU.","false","Biography information for The Earl of Dundee",,"The Earl of Dundee","HL6297"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713701","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-06","<p>The Government remains committed to driving reform, embedding stability and addressing shared challenges, such as security and migration, in Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH). At the 20 September 2016 General Affairs Council, the EU agreed that the Commission should issue a questionnaire to BiH authorities to assess the country's readiness to be granted candidate country status. That process is continuing. We will continue to support the reforms required through our bilateral engagement (including approximately £6.63 million in programme assistance in financial year 2016-17), in order to ensure BiH becomes a more stable, secure and prosperous country.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns","HL6297","2017-04-06T14:36:21.113Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713701/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713701/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713701/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-23","Bosnia and Herzegovina: EU Enlargement","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of any issues holding back the acceptance of Bosnia and Herzegovina as a candidate country to join the EU, including relating to constitutional and legal reform; and what assistance they are giving as a result.","false","Biography information for The Earl of Dundee",,"The Earl of Dundee","HL6298"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713702","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-04-04","<p>I refer the noble Lord to the answers given by my right hon. Friend the Minister for the Armed Forces (Mike Penning), in the House of Commons on 27 February 2017 to Question number 64193 and on 14 March 2017 to Question number 67005. The Army is consulting with the Departments for Education, Health and Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy.</p><p> </p><p>The Army is conducting a review of its Junior Entry policy to ensure it attracts the best young people and continues to maximise the talent of the individual, to the mutual advantage of both the young person and the Army. The review will report initial findings later this year.</p><p> </p><p>All recruits joining the Army, including those between the ages of 16 and 18, are recruited into a variety of roles depending on their aptitude and available vacancies. The Ministry of Defence does not make assessments of death and casualty rates in the context of recruitment practices.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2017-04-04T14:18:19.907Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713702/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713702/answer","Hansard Extracts -.docx","Hansard Extracts -.docx","Army: Young People","Army: Young People","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/713702/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-23","Army: Young People","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what arrangements they are making to ensure that the Army Review of Junior Entry (1) seeks and considers external evidence, (2) considers how the armed services can be exemplary standard setters in fulfilling their duty of care and support for young recruits, and (3) examines the proportion of young Army recruits who are destined for a future in the infantry; and what assessment they have made of the implications of the higher death and casualty rates in the infantry service for recruitment practices.","false","Biography information for Lord Judd",,"Lord Judd","HL6299"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714849","Department for International Development","false","2017-03-29","<p>DFID is developing a programme of support for people-to-people projects in Israel and the OPTs. UK support will help Israelis and Palestinians work together to achieve tangible improvements in their lives and build understanding between people on both sides of the conflict. The programme is aiming for launch at the beginning of next financial year.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-03-29T14:30:54.833Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714849/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714849/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714849/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-03-23","Israel: Palestinians","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what support her Department is providing to projects facilitating peaceful co-existence between Palestinians and Israelis.","false","Biography information for John Howell","Henley","John Howell","909549"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714850","Department for International Development","false","2017-03-29","<p>The way to end poverty and aid dependency is through inclusive economic growth, jobs, investment and trade. I recently launched DFID’s Economic Development Strategy which sets out my Department’s commitment to this agenda and the steps we are taking to deliver our priorities. Stronger economic development will enable the poorest countries to stand on their own two feet and is firmly in the UK’s national interest.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2017-03-29T14:28:11.197Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714850/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714850/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714850/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-03-23","Developing Countries: Economic Growth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps her Department is taking to promote economic development in developing countries.","false","Biography information for Chris Green","Bolton West","Chris Green","909548"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714851","Department for International Development","false","2017-03-29","<p>The way to end poverty and aid dependency is through inclusive economic growth, jobs, investment and trade. I recently launched DFID’s Economic Development Strategy which sets out my Department’s commitment to this agenda and the steps we are taking to deliver our priorities. Stronger economic development will enable the poorest countries to stand on their own two feet and is firmly in the UK’s national interest.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2017-03-29T14:29:17.757Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714851/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714851/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714851/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-03-23","Developing Countries: Economic Growth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps her Department is taking to promote economic development in developing countries.","false","Biography information for Henry Smith","Crawley","Henry Smith","909553"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714852","Department for International Development","false","2017-03-29","<p>We support UN Women as an important partner for the UK. As the campaign asks, we have put gender equality and the empowerment of women at the heart of our development policy and programming, and are achieving impressive results for women and girls at scale.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2017-03-29T15:40:16.233Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714852/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714852/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714852/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-03-23","Developing Countries: Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what support her Department is providing to the UN's Step It Up for Gender Equality initiative.","false","Biography information for Paula Sherriff","Dewsbury","Paula Sherriff","909554"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714853","Department for International Development","false","2017-03-29","<p>Protecting children is at the very heart of my department’s work. We have increased our efforts to directly tackle the exploitation of children, combatting the worst forms of child labour as part of the Prime Minister’s Modern Slavery agenda, and seeking to prevent violence and abuse against children in every setting.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2017-03-29T15:39:15.917Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714853/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714853/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714853/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-03-23","Developing Countries: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps her Department is taking to tackle child exploitation in developing countries.","false","Biography information for Mims Davies","Eastleigh","Mims Davies","909552"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714854","Department for International Development","false","2017-03-29","<p>We will honour our commitment to 0.7 per cent. Based on the Spending Review 2015 settlement, DFID will spend around 72 per cent of UK ODA in this financial year.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-03-29T14:32:47.05Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714854/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714854/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714854/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-03-23","Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how much and what proportion of the Official Development Assistance budget will be spent by her Department in 2017.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","909555"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714855","Department for International Development","false","2017-03-29","I am very clear that every pound of UK aid should go on saving and improving the lives of the poorest people in the world. All DFID projects are measured against a robust monitoring framework to ensure they remain cost effective. DFID also supports other aid spending departments, who are responsible for ensuring value for money and effective monitoring of their own aid spend.","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2017-03-29T14:26:06.69Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714855/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714855/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714855/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-03-23","Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps her Department is taking to ensure value for money of UK aid through strengthened monitoring.","false","Biography information for Michael Tomlinson","Mid Dorset and North Poole","Michael Tomlinson","909547"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714856","Department for International Development","false","2017-03-29","<p>Britain is one of the leading donors helping developing countries to raise more tax revenue. The UK has committed to doubling its efforts on tax capacity building by 2020, in line with commitments made in the Addis Tax Initiative. We are working closely with Treasury and HMRC to assist partner countries, donors and international organisations to make rapid progress together.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2017-03-29T15:37:33.327Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714856/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714856/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714856/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-03-23","Developing Countries: Tax Collection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps her Department is taking to help developing countries raise more tax revenue.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","909546"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714366","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-28","<p>I am in regular communication with the Secretary of State for International Trade, my Rt. Hon Friend the member for North Somerset (Dr Liam Fox) on these issues.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-03-28T14:12:48.777Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714366/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714366/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714366/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-22","Yemen: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with the Secretary of State for International Trade on UK arms sales to countries that are part of the Saudi-led coalition operating in Yemen.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","909525"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714367","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-28","<p>Illegal wildlife trade is a serious threat to the world’s endangered species and combating it is a priority for the Foreign and Commonwealth Office. It is a serious criminal industry worth more than £6 billion a year. It is fuelled by corruption and undermines good governance and the rule of law. We work with our overseas network, the Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs and the Department for International Development to secure global action to combat it.</p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson",,"2017-03-28T14:34:51.773Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714367/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714367/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714367/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-22","Nature Conservation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what role his Department has in the protection of endangered species abroad.","false","Biography information for Mr Ranil Jayawardena","North East Hampshire","Mr Ranil Jayawardena","909524"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714368","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-28","<p>We support the recommendations of the Rakhine Advisory Commission. I discussed the report with the Chair of the Commission, Kofi Annan, on 16 March. We stand ready to provide assistance to enable the Burmese authorities to implement its recommendations. We also look forward to the final report.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-03-28T14:32:25.917Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714368/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714368/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714368/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-22","Burma: Politics and Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what the implications for his policies are of the interim report and recommendations of the Advisory Commission on Rakhine State, published on 16 March 2017; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Paul Scully","Sutton and Cheam","Paul Scully","909531"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714369","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-28","<p>The FCO is working closely with the Department for International Development to provide life-saving emergency aid for those affected by drought and to encourage the international community urgently to step-up their assistance. In his recent visit to the region the Foreign Secretary, my Rt Hon. Friend the Member for Uxbridge and South Ruislip (Boris Johnson), emphasised the UK’s steadfast support during this unprecedented humanitarian crisis.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-03-28T14:20:14.07Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714369/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714369/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714369/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-22","East Africa: Droughts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps his Department is taking to assist east African nations affected by drought.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","909526"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714370","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-28","<p>The Foreign Secretary regularly meets his EU counterparts. Next week he will attend the Foreign Affairs Council in Brussels and meet the German Foreign Minister in London.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-03-28T14:47:15.547Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714370/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714370/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714370/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-22","UK Relations with EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, when he next plans to meet his EU counterparts; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Michael Fabricant","Lichfield","Michael Fabricant","909532"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714371","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-28","<p>There is a worrying trend of persecution of the Baha’i faith in Iran, which includes the harassment of Baha’i school children and students. We call on Iran to cease harassment of all religious minorities and to allow freedom of religion to all Iranians. I raised our concerns in Tehran on 18 Jan.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-03-28T14:26:10.1Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714371/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714371/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714371/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-22","Iran: Baha'i Faith","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent reports he has received on harassment of schoolchildren and expulsion of university students from the Baha'i community in Iran; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","909527"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714372","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-28","<p>The security situation in Yemen remains a concern. The conflict continues to have a grave impact on the civilian population and makes humanitarian access and delivery of aid in to and within Yemen extremely difficult.</p><p>A political solution is the best way to bring long-term stability. The UK is playing a leading role in diplomatic efforts, supporting the UN Special Envoy’s tireless efforts to achieve this. The Foreign Secretary, my Rt Hon. Friend the Member for Uxbridge and South Ruislip (Boris Johnson), met his Quint counterparts from Oman, Saudi Arabia, United Arab Emirates, US and UN in Bonn on 16 February.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-03-28T14:24:42.05Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714372/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714372/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714372/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-22","Yemen: Politics and Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the political and security situation in Yemen.","false","Biography information for Gill Furniss","Sheffield, Brightside and Hillsborough","Gill Furniss","909523"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714373","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-28","<p>The theme of the UK Presidency of the UN Security Council has been conflict prevention in Africa, with focus on the Lake Chad Basin, South Sudan, and Somalia. The UK has also held an open debate on modern slavery, to place the issue firmly on the Council’s agenda. Throughout our Presidency, we have been action-oriented, transparent and consultative.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-03-28T14:30:10.65Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714373/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714373/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714373/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-22","UN Security Council","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what his priorities have been during the UK's Presidency of the UN Security Council in March 2017.","false","Biography information for Dr James Davies","Vale of Clwyd","Dr James Davies","909529"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714374","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-03-28","<p>We continue to call on the Governments of Israel and Egypt to show maximum flexibility in opening the crossings into Gaza. Officials from our Embassy in Tel Aviv most recently raised the issue of movement and access with the Israeli authorities on 13 March.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-03-28T14:16:55.46Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714374/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714374/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/714374/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-03-22","Gaza: Travel Restrictions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps the Government is taking to promote greater freedom of movement for civilians entering and leaving Gaza.","false","Biography information for Kate Hollern","Blackburn","Kate Hollern","909530"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712868","Attorney General","false","2017-03-28","<p>I refer the hon. Member to my Answer of 20 March to PQ 68035.</p><p> </p><p>FoI statistics do not refer to requests responded to within 30 days as the statutory deadline is 20 days.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2017-03-28T15:44:40.087Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712868/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712868/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712868/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2017-03-21","Attorney General: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, on how many occasions the Law Officers' Departments took longer than 30 working days to respond to a freedom of information request in each month since July 2016.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","68662"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712869","Cabinet Office","false","2017-03-27","<p>I refer the hon. Member to my Answer of 21 March 2017 to PQ68036.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore","68672","2017-03-27T09:06:39.2Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712869/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712869/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712869/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-03-21","Cabinet Office: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, on how many occasions his Department took longer than 30 working days to respond to a freedom of information request in each month since July 2016.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","68663"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712870","Cabinet Office","false","2017-03-28","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-03-28T12:31:52.957Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712870/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712870/answer","PQ68642 V.02 (1).pdf","PQ68642 V.02 (1).pdf","UKSA Response to PQ68642","UKSA Response to PQ68642","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712870/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-03-21","Death: Pendle","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many deaths in the Pendle area were (a) alcohol and (b) drug-related in each of the last five years; and how many of those deaths were of people aged (i) under 18, (ii) 18 to 24, (iii) 25 to 40 and (iv) over 40 years old.","false","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","68642"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712871","Cabinet Office","false","2017-04-25","<p>The Cabinet Office does not hold information regarding government departments’ budgets for newspaper advertising in the 2017/18 financial year.</p><p> </p><p>Departmental marketing communications teams, working with their media planning and buying agencies, take decisions about which kinds of media and specific channels will be used within their communications campaigns to best reach their target audiences, once their campaign strategies have been defined.</p><p> </p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-04-25T14:40:03.09Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712871/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712871/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712871/answer","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712871/answer/previousversion/42261","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-03-21","Newspaper Press: Advertising","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what information his Department holds on the budget the Government has for advertising in newspapers for each government department in the 2017-18 financial year.","false","Biography information for Clive Lewis","Norwich South","Clive Lewis","68736"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712872","Cabinet Office","false","2017-04-25","<p>In the full 2015/16 financial year, government spending on advertising in the Evening Standard newspaper totalled £297,037 (spending on print advertising and digital advertising where it was bought directly). This equated to approximately 0.22% of all media buying for government advertising in that financial year.</p><p> </p><p>I am aware of the comments that the Hon. Member has made in the media on the appointment of the new editor of the <em>Evening Standard</em>. I would note that any spending on advertising is in line with the Government Communication Service’s Propriety Guidance. In addition, departmental Accounting Officers have a particular responsibility for the propriety of using public resources for advertising, as well as for the economy, efficiency and effectiveness of their use. The resources employed should be proportional to the objectives or policy of the programme involved and justifiable on value-for-money grounds. I believe this provides an appropriate system of checks to avoid any conflict of interest and ensure taxpayers’ money is properly spent.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-04-25T14:33:42.247Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712872/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712872/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712872/answer","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712872/answer/previousversion/42262","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-03-21","Government Departments: Evening Standard","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how much the Government spent on advertising in the Evening Standard newspaper in the last financial year for which information is available.","false","Biography information for Clive Lewis","Norwich South","Clive Lewis","68738"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712873","HM Treasury","false","2017-03-24","<p>The Treasury does not hold the information requested.</p><p> </p>","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby",,"2017-03-24T14:06:16.78Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712873/answer","Biography information for Simon Kirby","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712873/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712873/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-03-21","Treasury: Advertising","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what budget his Department has for advertising in newspapers in the (a) 2016-17 and (b) 2017-18 financial year.","false","Biography information for Clive Lewis","Norwich South","Clive Lewis","68737"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712874","HM Treasury","false","2017-03-29","<p>The Marriage Allowance was introduced in 2015-16 to recognise the importance of marriage in the tax system. Around 1.8m people have claimed the allowance to date.</p><p> </p><p>Our current best estimate assessment of the initial cost of this allowance is £140m in 2015-16, but this does not include the impact of any expected future claims, which can be backdated to this year. The total cost of this allowance is forecast to rise to £385m in 2015-16 once these claims are taken into account.</p><p> </p><p>An estimate of the initial cost of this allowance for 2016-17 will not be available until the end of the tax year. We forecast an eventual cost to the exchequer of £425m, once all backdated claims are taken into account.</p><p> </p><p>HM Treasury does not hold information relating to the income deciles of claimants or successful applicants of the Marriage Allowance. Previous analysis of the total eligible population has shown the majority of the benefits of this policy go to the bottom half of the income distribution. Only basic rate taxpayers and non-taxpayers will benefit.</p><p> </p><p>HM Treasury does not hold information about either how many individuals claiming Universal Credit are eligible for the Marriage Allowance, or how many are in receipt of it.</p><p> </p><p>The income decile profile of claimants of Married Couple's Allowance is set out below for the latest year available (2014-15):</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td colspan="2"><p> </p></td><td colspan="2"><p> </p></td><td colspan="2"><p> </p></td><td colspan="2"><p> </p></td><td colspan="2"><p> </p></td><td colspan="3"><p>Percentage</p></td></tr><tr><td rowspan="2"><p><strong>Percentile Groups (ranged on total income before tax)</strong></p></td><td><p> </p></td><td colspan="2"><p> </p></td><td colspan="2"><p> </p></td><td colspan="2"><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td colspan="2"><p> </p></td><td 