"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712878","HM Treasury","false","2017-03-24","<p>Recognising a risk of non-compliance within the residential rental market, HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) launched the Let Property Campaign in September 2013 focused on the residential property letting market.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC have collected a range of data relating to the whole landlord population including licensing data. The data is being used to identify landlords who have not reported the rental income they should have to HMRC. The Campaign has encouraged over 26,000 residential landlords to voluntarily come forward and disclose previously unreported rental income and unpaid tax on their rental income. In addition, the Campaign has generated £115m in additional tax, interest and penalties since its launch.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2017-03-24T14:38:30.027Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712878/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712878/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712878/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-03-21","Landlords: Newham","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will make an assessment of the effect of the Landlord Licensing Scheme introduced by the London Borough of Newham on supporting HM Revenue and Customs identify underpayment of tax by landlords.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","68741"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712879","HM Treasury","false","2017-03-29","<p>Since its introduction in 1996, the Landfill Communities Fund (LCF) has contributed over £1.4 billion to community projects.</p><p> </p><p>The value for money provided by the LCF is assessed in the same manner as all other Government funding.</p><p> </p><p>Despite difficult decisions on spending, at Budget 2017 the Government decided to maintain the value of the LCF at £39.3 million for 2017-18. This means the cap on contributions from landfill operators has increased from 4.2% to 5.3%. The Government expects to maintain this 5.3% cap for future years, but this expectation assumes we see continued progress from environmental bodies in reducing administrative costs and the level of unspent funds.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2017-03-29T13:40:42.97Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712879/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712879/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712879/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-03-21","Landfill Communities Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether he made an assessment of the potential merits of increasing the diversion rate for the Landfill Communities Fund prior to the introduction of the Spring Budget 2017.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","68646"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712880","HM Treasury","false","2017-03-29","<p>I refer the hon. Member to my Answer of 23 March 2017 to PQ UIN 68052.</p><p> </p>","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby",,"2017-03-29T15:44:45.443Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712880/answer","Biography information for Simon Kirby","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712880/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712880/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-03-21","Treasury: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, on how many occasions his Department took longer than 30 working days to respond to a freedom of information request in each month since July 2016.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","68674"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712882","HM Treasury","false","2017-03-29","<p>The Government published the discussion paper “Tax issues for late-life oil and gas assets” on 20 March. This considers whether any changes to the oil and gas tax rules could facilitate the transfer of late life assets and support the Government’s aim of Maximising Economic Recovery from the UK’s oil and gas reserves.</p><p> </p><p>The discussion paper is available here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/tax-issues-for-late-life-oil-and-gas-assets" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/tax-issues-for-late-life-oil-and-gas-assets</a></p><p> </p><p>The Government recognises the importance of engaging fully with individuals, practitioners, businesses and other organisations in considering developments in tax policy. We welcome responses from all interested parties to this document.</p><p> </p><p>The Government will establish a panel of industry experts to consider the tax issues identified in the paper. It will consist of upstream oil and gas tax experts, tax practitioners and businesses with considerable experience of late-life oil and gas asset transactions.</p><p> </p><p>The terms of reference for the expert panel have been published alongside the discussion paper. The panel will be established shortly.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","68798 ; 68799","2017-03-29T13:27:40.197Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712882/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712882/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712882/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-03-21","North Sea Oil","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to paragraph 3.29 of Spring Budget 2017, if he will make it his policy to engage with non-industry representatives, including non-governmental organisations with expertise in environmental, energy and consumer rights issues when consulting on the formation of future North Sea oil and gas policy.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","68797"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712883","HM Treasury","false","2017-03-29","<p>The Government published the discussion paper “Tax issues for late-life oil and gas assets” on 20 March. This considers whether any changes to the oil and gas tax rules could facilitate the transfer of late life assets and support the Government’s aim of Maximising Economic Recovery from the UK’s oil and gas reserves.</p><p> </p><p>The discussion paper is available here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/tax-issues-for-late-life-oil-and-gas-assets" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/tax-issues-for-late-life-oil-and-gas-assets</a></p><p> </p><p>The Government recognises the importance of engaging fully with individuals, practitioners, businesses and other organisations in considering developments in tax policy. We welcome responses from all interested parties to this document.</p><p> </p><p>The Government will establish a panel of industry experts to consider the tax issues identified in the paper. It will consist of upstream oil and gas tax experts, tax practitioners and businesses with considerable experience of late-life oil and gas asset transactions.</p><p> </p><p>The terms of reference for the expert panel have been published alongside the discussion paper. The panel will be established shortly.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","68797 ; 68798","2017-03-29T13:27:40.353Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712883/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712883/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712883/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-03-21","North Sea Oil: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to paragraph 3.29 of Spring Budget 2017, when he plans to publish the formal discussion paper on the allowing of transfers of tax history between buyers and sellers of North Sea oil and gas assets.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","68799"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712884","HM Treasury","false","2017-03-29","<p>The Government published the discussion paper “Tax issues for late-life oil and gas assets” on 20 March. This considers whether any changes to the oil and gas tax rules could facilitate the transfer of late life assets and support the Government’s aim of Maximising Economic Recovery from the UK’s oil and gas reserves.</p><p> </p><p>The discussion paper is available here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/tax-issues-for-late-life-oil-and-gas-assets" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/tax-issues-for-late-life-oil-and-gas-assets</a></p><p> </p><p>The Government recognises the importance of engaging fully with individuals, practitioners, businesses and other organisations in considering developments in tax policy. We welcome responses from all interested parties to this document.</p><p> </p><p>The Government will establish a panel of industry experts to consider the tax issues identified in the paper. It will consist of upstream oil and gas tax experts, tax practitioners and businesses with considerable experience of late-life oil and gas asset transactions.</p><p> </p><p>The terms of reference for the expert panel have been published alongside the discussion paper. The panel will be established shortly.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","68797 ; 68799","2017-03-29T13:27:40.057Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712884/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712884/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712884/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-03-21","Fossil Fuels: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to paragraph 3.29 of Spring Budget 2017, by what criteria members will be appointed to the new advisory panel on oil and gas tax policy; and when he plans for that new advisory panel to be established.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","68798"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712885","HM Treasury","false","2017-03-29","<p>Exiting the EU will present both opportunities and challenges, but the UK will remain an open country, and an attractive location to invest and do business, in part due to our competitive tax regime and access to skilled talent.</p><p> </p><p>The independent Office for Budget Responsibility’s March forecast projected corporation tax receipts to increase from £53.6bn in 2016-17 to £54.7bn in 2021-22.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2017-03-29T13:29:00.117Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712885/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712885/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712885/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-03-21","Corporation Tax","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the potential effect on corporation tax receipts of UK companies creating headquarter subsidiaries in EU countries after the UK exits the EU.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Edwards","Carmarthen East and Dinefwr","Jonathan Edwards","68781"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712886","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-04-26","<p>In a speech on the 28 March 2017 the Secretary of State said that he will look to ensure Help to Buy Equity Loans are only used to support new build houses on acceptable terms.</p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell",,"2017-04-26T12:50:48.607Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712886/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712886/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712886/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-03-21","Help to Buy Scheme: Leasehold","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will make it his policy to stop providing Government support through the Help to Buy scheme for new houses sold on a leasehold basis.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","68793"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712887","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-03-28","<p>The National Planning Policy Framework provides strong protection for irreplaceable habitats such as ancient woodland and veteran trees. In addition, on 7 February we published the Housing White Paper, <em>Fixing our broken housing market</em>. Through this we are consulting on placing our policy to include ancient woodland and veteran trees alongside other national policies which the Government regards as providing a strong reason to restrict development when preparing plans, or which indicate that development should be restricted when making decisions on planning applications. These policies include those on Sites of Special Scientific Interest, Green Belt, National Parks and designated heritage assets. The consultation closes on 2 May, and is available at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/590464/Fixing_our_broken_housing_market_-_print_ready_version.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/590464/Fixing_our_broken_housing_market_-_print_ready_version.pdf</a></p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell",,"2017-03-28T13:47:16.79Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712887/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712887/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712887/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-03-21","Forests: Planning Permission","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what steps he is taking to ensure that ancient woods and veteran trees are protected from development in planning policy.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","68801"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712888","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-03-29","<p>I refer the hon. Member to my answer to Question UIN 68038 on 24 March 2017.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-03-29T14:17:30.667Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712888/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712888/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712888/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-03-21","Department for Communities and Local Government: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, on how many occasions his Department took longer than 30 working days to respond to a freedom of information request in each month since July 2016.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","68664"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712889","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-03-24","<p>The £2.3 billion Housing Infrastructure Fund, announced at Autumn Statement 2016, will deliver up to 100,000 additional new homes through targeted investment in infrastructure in the areas of greatest housing need. It will support local authorities who are ambitious to meet their identified housing need, or go further, and those who have the strategic vision to work together. Local authorities will be able to bid for grant funding to support delivery of physical infrastructure necessary to unlock housing growth. Details of how the fund will operate will be set out when it is launched later this spring.</p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell",,"2017-03-24T09:41:05.343Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712889/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712889/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712889/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-03-21","Housing Infrastructure Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, who will be eligible for funding from the Housing Infrastructure Fund.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","68745"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712890","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-04-04","<p>The Government is committed to building a strong private rented sector, which provides security and stability for both tenants and landlords.</p><p>To promote responsible lettings, we have issued ‘How to Rent’ guidance on gov.uk and made it a legal requirement, since 1 October 2014, for letting and managing agents in England to belong to one of the three Government approved redress schemes, which offer a clear route for landlords and tenants to pursue complaints. The Government announced at Autumn Statement 2016 a ban on letting agent fees paid by tenants, to improve competition in the private rental market and give renters greater clarity and control over what they will pay. And most recently, the Government announced on 28 March that we will make Client Money Protection mandatory for letting and managing agents that handle client money; this will ensure that every agent is giving tenants and landlords the financial protection that they deserve.</p><p>The Government is committed to taking action to tackle rogue landlords and agents; the Housing &amp; Planning Act 2016 introduced further powers to help crack down on rogue landlords, including a database of rogue landlords and property agents, banning orders for the most serious and prolific offenders, civil penalties of up to £30,000 and extended rent repayment orders.</p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell",,"2017-04-04T15:34:07.557Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712890/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712890/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712890/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-03-21","Landlords: Regulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what steps his Department is taking to (a) promote responsible letting and (b) deal with rogue landlords.","false","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","68702"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712891","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-03-24","<p>The Department does not maintain records of the total number of correspondence received concerning complains about library service changes for either all or each local authority in England.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2017-03-24T13:00:42.59Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712891/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712891/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712891/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-03-21","Public Libraries: Complaints","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, pursuant to the Answer of 20 March 2017 to Question 68114, on public libraries: complaints, what the total number of correspondence received by her Department from all local authorities complaining about library services changes since 2010 is.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","68689"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712892","Department of Health","false","2017-03-24","<p>The data published by the Office for National Statistics (ONS) on 17 March builds on our knowledge of groups at high risk of suicide and where this may relate to their occupation, which we set out in the Cross-Government National Suicide Prevention Strategy in 2012.</p><p> </p><p>Alongside the ONS data, Public Health England published suicide prevention and postvention toolkits for employers. <em>Reducing the risk of suicide: a toolkit for employers</em> and <em>Crisis management in the event of a suicide: a postvention toolkit for employers</em> are attached.</p><p> </p><p>Departmental officials have been working with Public Health England to assess what impact this new data will have on our policies and we will continue to do that as we implement the National Strategy.</p><p> </p><p>We published the updated National Suicide Prevention Strategy in January which set out how we will strengthen its delivery in key areas, including better targeting of high risk groups. Within the updated strategy we stated we will be working with industry to share best practice with other sectors such as Network Rail and the construction industry. We will provide further updates on developments through our annual suicide prevention progress reports.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-03-24T11:43:03.78Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712892/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712892/answer","PHE suicide prevention toolkit.pdf ; PHE suicide postvention toolkit.pdf","PHE suicide prevention toolkit.pdf ; PHE suicide postvention toolkit.pdf","PHE suicide prevention toolkit ; PHE suicide postvention toolkit","PHE suicide prevention toolkit ; PHE suicide postvention toolkit","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712892/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-21","Suicide: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the implications for his policies are of the data from the Office for National Statistics on the disproportionately high rate of suicide among women in the culture, media and sport sectors; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","68627"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712893","Home Office","false","2017-03-28","<p>The Home Office publishes National Statistics on alcohol and late night refreshment licensing in England and Wales on an annual basis.</p><p> </p><p>The information requested can be found in Table 1 of the <em>Alcohol and late night refreshment licensing, England and Wales, 31 March 2016</em> publication and can be accessed using the following link <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/alcohol-and-late-night-refreshment-licensing-england-and-wales-31-march-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/alcohol-and-late-night-refreshment-licensing-england-and-wales-31-march-2016</a>.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2017-03-28T15:01:26.647Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712893/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712893/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712893/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-03-21","Licensed Premises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many premises authorising the sale or supply of alcohol by means of a (a) premises licence or (b) club premises certificate there were in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","68789"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712894","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-28","<p>In keeping with the UK's Declaration of Commitment to end sexual violence in conflict, all UK Service personnel receive detailed instruction on International Humanitarian Law which absolutely prohibits sexual violence. We have also developed more specific training on preventing sexual violence, exploitation and abuse, which has been delivered to Service personnel dependent upon the requirements of deployments. Since August 2016, all pre-deployment training provided by the Mission Training and Mobilisation Centre has included specific training on preventing and responding to sexual violence in conflict. This has been delivered to around 4,000 UK personnel.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-03-28T15:29:00.257Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712894/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712894/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712894/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-21","Armed Conflict: Sexual Offences","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many armed forces personnel from the (a) Royal Navy, (b) Army and (c) RAF have received training as part of the Preventing Sexual Violence in Conflict initiative.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","68804"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712895","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-28","<p>The UK currently has around 400 Service personnel deployed to UN Missions around the world. All have received training on International Humanitarian Law, which absolutely prohibits sexual violence. Many have also received specific instruction on the prevention of and response to conflict-related sexual violence, depending on the requirements of their deployment.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-03-28T15:30:17.163Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712895/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712895/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712895/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-21","Armed Conflict: Sexual Offences","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many armed forces personnel currently deployed as part of UN missions have received training as part of the Preventing Sexual Violence in Conflict initiative.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","68805"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712896","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-28","<p>All UK Service personnel deploying to the UN mission in South Sudan (UNMISS), numbering up to 400, will receive specific instruction on the prevention of and response to conflict-related sexual violence as part of their pre-deployment training.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-03-28T15:29:34.383Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712896/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712896/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712896/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-21","Armed Conflict: Sexual Offences","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many armed forces personnel due to be deployed to South Sudan have received training as part of the Preventing Sexual Violence in Conflict initiative.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","68806"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712897","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-28","<p>The numbers of Regular and Reserve Army personnel who were qualified for Guided Multiple Launch Rocket System (MLRS) roles over the last five years is shown below:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Date</strong></p></td><td><p>01/04/2012</p></td><td><p>01/04/2013</p></td><td><p>01/04/2014</p></td><td><p>01/04/2015</p></td><td><p>01/04/2016</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>MLRS trained personnel</strong></p></td><td><p>190</p></td><td><p>180</p></td><td><p>170</p></td><td><p>150</p></td><td><p>160</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-03-28T15:31:08.927Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712897/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712897/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712897/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-21","Armed Forces: Guided Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many fully trained personnel qualified for Guided Multiple Launch Rocket System roles there were in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","68802"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712898","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-28","<p>As at 1 March 2017 there were around 660 Army Reservists recorded as currently holding the qualification to operate the 105mm light gun in use by the Army.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-03-28T15:31:41.173Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712898/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712898/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712898/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-21","Armed Forces: Artillery","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Army reservists are currently qualified to operate the 105 mm light gun.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","68803"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712899","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-28","<p>A feasibility study into a Wildcat tactical data link has recently been concluded.This study is in the early stages of assessment by the Royal Navy and therefore no timetable has been set.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-03-28T15:40:54.987Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712899/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712899/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712899/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-21","Wildcat Helicopters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the timetable is for the installation of a tactical data link on board the fleet of Leonardo Wildcat helicopters.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","68787"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712900","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-27","<p>The total cost of applying thermal metal spray to the Queen Elizabeth Class aircraft carriers includes the development and build of application equipment, preparation of the flight deck surface and application of the coating.</p><p>I am withholding the detailed cost information, as its disclosure at this time would prejudice the commercial interests of the Ministry of Defence.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-03-27T15:21:18.417Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712900/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712900/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712900/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-21","HMS Queen Elizabeth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the cost is of applying thermal metal coating on the landing areas of HMS Queen Elizabeth.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","68788"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712901","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-28","<p>The Queen Elizabeth Class (QEC) aircraft carriers are designed to enable the operation of fixed wing and rotary wing aircraft. Both the QEC aircraft carriers will have the capability to integrate and support battlefield helicopters.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-03-28T15:41:31.583Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712901/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712901/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712901/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-21","Aircraft Carriers: Helicopters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what modifications will be required for the Queen Elizabeth-class carriers to provide battlefield helicopter operations.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","68785"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712902","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-28","<p>We currently have 11 pilots, 81 maintenance engineers and 14 logistics and support staff training with the United States Marine Corps on the F-35 Lightning at Marine Corps Air Station Beaufort. There are no software programmers training with the US Marine Corps.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-03-28T15:42:13.44Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712902/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712902/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712902/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-21","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many (a) pilots, (b) maintenance engineers, (c) software programmers and (d) logistics and support staff from his Department are currently training with the US Marine Corps on the F35B Lightning II programme.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","68786"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712903","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-03-28","<p>There are several rotary-wing platforms within the Department's inventory that would be capable of fulfilling a maritime intra-theatre lift solution for the UK's Carrier Strike Group.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-03-28T15:42:50.743Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712903/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712903/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/712903/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-03-21","Aircraft Carriers: Helicopters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, which platforms he is considering to provide for a Maritime intra-theatre list solution for carrier strike groups.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","68780"
